history.content:
If you want to change sections when you are waitlisted, you drop the course and rewaitlist for the other section.

Whether or not that's the best course of action depends on a variety of factors, such as your current waitlist position for your section vs the waitlist position for the section that you want to switch to.

children.subject:
It would place you at the end of the waitlist for the course.

The way the waitlist works is: if there is space that you can enroll in (and no one ahead of you in the waitlist can), then when the waitlist next processes, you would be let into the class.

Thanks!

Here's a subjective question: assuming there's enough space in a new section I choose, how likely do you think it is I'll get in the class considering I'll have to move to the end of the class waitlist? (since there also needs to be space in the class when I'm processed AND there needs to be space in my selected section)

@student answer: where would re-enrolling place me in the waitlist for the class overall? Also, assuming there's space for me in a section how would I be affected by the answer to my 1st question (if I would be at all)?
You can also see the student answer to @5606 for a similar situation as yours.

My advice would be to drop and re-enroll into the open section as that gives you a better chance of enrolling into the class, even though your waitlist position in the class is going to be much higher than what it is now. The reason for this is, once the space in that open section frees up (70% rule is de-enforced), you'd get into the class in the order of the waitlist for that section regardless of your waitlist position in the class.
